HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 313
BY REPRESENTATIVE MILLER
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Lemelle family of St. Landry Parish on the occasion of their pilgrimage
to Rome and audience with His Holiness Pope Leo XIV.
WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana takes great
pride in recognizing individuals and families whose heritage and accomplishments bring
honor and distinction to the state; and
WHEREAS, His Holiness Pope Leo XIV shares ancestral ties with the esteemed
Lemelle family of St. Landry Parish, Louisiana, which is a family that has deep roots in the
rich cultural and spiritual heritage of the state; and
WHEREAS, the Lemelle family has preserved a proud legacy of faith, perseverance,
family unity, and service that reflects the enduring values of the people of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, the historic and meaningful connection between Pope Leo XIV and the
Lemelle family serves as a source of pride and inspiration for the citizens of St. Landry
Parish and the state of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, the Lemelle family is traveling to Rome, Italy, on a sacred pilgrimage
that will culminate with the distinguished honor of being granted an audience at the Vatican
with the Holy Father on June 17, 2026; and
WHEREAS, the Lemelle family is deserving of heartfelt recognition as they
undertake this memorable pilgrimage and celebrate an extraordinary moment in their family
history, and the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana proudly commends
the family for bringing honor to St. Landry Parish and the state through their faith, heritage,
and continued devotion to the values of family and community.
